Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
saveWorkspace(25.10)                                      saveWorkspace(25.10)

Name
       saveWorkspace - Saves the named workspace to the specified directory

Syntax
       saveWorkspace

       [-help]

       -name <workspaceName>

       [-dir <directory>]

       Saves the named workspace to the specified directory. You can then load
       the  workspace  whenever you want from the specified directory by using
       the loadWorkspace command. A workspace contains customized main  window
       settings including:

              * Size and placement of window

              * Specific orientation of toolbars

              * Docking status

              * Visibility settings

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each saveWorkspace parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man saveWorkspace

       -name <workspaceName>
              Specifies the name of the workspace to be saved.

       -dir <directory>
              Specifies the directory in which the workspace is to be saved.

              Default: Current working directory

Example
       The  following  example  saves the current window settings to the Test-
       Workspace in the current working directory.

       saveWorkspace -name TestWorkspace

